For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all enzymes in UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot annotated to catalyze reactions involving that lipid.
This query does not consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions and enzymes only for the specified lipid.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

# Example 16
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?uniprot
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?startId owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
  # federated query to UniProt
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?uniprot up:reviewed true .
    ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
  }
} 
ORDER BY ?startId

natural_language_question:
For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all corresponding reactions (Rhea IDs and equation).
This query does consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions involving the specified lipid and/or its more specific forms.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>

# Example 5
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?id ?name ?chebi ?rhea ?rheaEquation 
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # Retrieve children lipids 
  ?id rdfs:subClassOf* ?startId .
  ?id rdfs:label ?name .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?id owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:equation ?rheaEquation .
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
} 
ORDER BY  ?startId ?id
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?rhea ?equation
WHERE {
  # Identify the ChEBI ID for Ceramide (CHEBI:17761) and its more specific forms (subclasses)
  # The user specified SWISSLIPID:000399814, which maps to Ceramide (CHEBI:17761).
  # The rdfs:subClassOf* property ensures that reactions involving Ceramide itself
  # or any of its subclasses are included.
  ?chebi_id rdfs:subClassOf* CHEBI:17761 .

  # Find Rhea reactions that involve these ChEBI compounds.
  # The path (rh:chebi | rh:reactivePart/rh:chebi | rh:underlyingChebi/rh:chebi)
  # covers different ways ChEBI identifiers are linked to compounds in Rhea.
  ?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound (rh:chebi | rh:reactivePart/rh:chebi | rh:underlyingChebi/rh:chebi) ?chebi_id .
  
  # Retrieve the chemical equation for the identified reactions.
  ?rhea rh:equation ?equation .
}

natural_language_question: What are the Homo sapiens genes associated with cancer and their orthologs expressed in the Rattus norvegicus brain?
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX orthodb: <http://purl.orthodb.org/>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?humanGeneLabel ?orthologGeneLabel ?diseaseComment ?anatomicEntityLabel
WHERE {
  # --- UniProt: Find Homo sapiens proteins associated with cancer ---
  ?humanProtein a up:Protein ;
                up:organism taxon:9606 ; # Homo sapiens
                up:encodedBy ?humanGene ;
                up:annotation ?annotation .
  ?annotation a up:Disease_Annotation ;
              rdfs:comment ?diseaseComment .
  FILTER (CONTAINS(LCASE(?diseaseComment), "cancer"))
  
  ?humanGene skos:prefLabel ?humanGeneLabel .

  # --- OrthoDB: Find orthologs of the human proteins ---
  SERVICE <https://sparql.orthodb.org/sparql> {
    ?orthoGroup orthodb:hasMember ?memberHuman .
    ?memberHuman orthodb:xref/orthodb:xrefResource ?humanProtein . # Join with UniProt human protein
    
    ?orthoGroup orthodb:hasMember ?memberOrtholog .
    ?memberOrtholog orthodb:xref/orthodb:xrefResource ?orthologProtein .
  }

  # --- UniProt (continued): Get details for the ortholog protein and link to Ensembl gene ---
  ?orthologProtein a up:Protein ;
                   up:organism taxon:10116 ; # Rattus norvegicus
                   up:encodedBy ?orthologGene .
  
  ?orthologGene skos:prefLabel ?orthologGeneLabel .
  
  # Link ortholog protein to its Ensembl gene, which is needed for Bgee
  ?orthologProtein rdfs:seeAlso ?orthologEnsemblXref .
  ?orthologEnsemblXref up:transcribedFrom ?orthologEnsemblGene .

  # --- Bgee: Check expression of ortholog genes in Rattus norvegicus brain ---
  SERVICE <https://www.bgee.org/sparql> {
    ?orthologGeneBgee lscr:xrefEnsemblGene ?orthologEnsemblGene . # Join with the Ensembl gene from UniProt
    ?orthologGeneBgee genex:isExpressedIn ?anatomicEntity .
    ?anatomicEntity rdfs:label ?anatomicEntityLabel .
    
    # Filter for brain expression (case-insensitive)
    FILTER (CONTAINS(LCASE(?anatomicEntityLabel), "brain"))
  }
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve human enzymes that metabolize sphingolipids and are annotated in ChEMBL
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX cco: <http://rdf.ebi.ac.uk/terms/chembl#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?protein ?proteinName ?reaction ?chebi ?chebiLabel
WHERE {
  # UniProt: Retrieve human enzymes and their catalyzed reactions
  ?protein up:organism taxon:9606 . # Human proteins
  ?protein up:annotation ?annotation .
  ?annotation a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation . # Ensure it's a catalytic activity annotation (i.e., an enzyme)
  ?annotation up:catalyticActivity ?catalyticActivity .
  ?catalyticActivity up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction . # Link to Rhea reaction
  OPTIONAL { ?protein up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?proteinName . } # Get protein full name

  # Rhea: Filter reactions involving sphingolipids
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
    ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
    ?chebi rdfs:subClassOf* CHEBI:52639 . # Filter for sphingolipids or their subclasses
    OPTIONAL { ?chebi rdfs:label ?chebiLabel . } # Get ChEBI label
  }

  # IDSM/ChEMBL: Filter proteins annotated in ChEMBL
  SERVICE <https://idsm.elixir-czech.cz/sparql/endpoint/idsm> {
    ?activity a cco:Activity .
    ?activity cco:hasAssay ?assay .
    ?assay cco:hasTarget ?target .
    ?target cco:hasTargetComponent/cco:targetCmptXref ?protein . # Join on ?protein (UniProt ID)
    ?protein a cco:UniprotRef . # Ensure the target component is a UniProt reference
  }
}

natural_language_question: Find mouse homologs in OMABrowser of human enzymes that catalyze reactions involving sterols (CHEBI:15889). Federating with Rhea and OMABrowser.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

SELECT
  DISTINCT
    ?chebi
    ?reaction
    ?humanProtein
    ?mouseProtein
    ?cluster 
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
    ?reaction rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
    ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
    ?chebi rdfs:subClassOf* CHEBI:15889
  }

  ?humanProtein up:organism taxon:9606 .
  ?humanProtein up:annotation ?a .
  ?a a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation .
  ?a up:catalyticActivity ?ca .
  ?ca up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction .

  SERVICE  <https://sparql.omabrowser.org/sparql> {
    ?cluster a orth:ParalogsCluster .
    ?cluster orth:hasHomologousMember ?node1 , ?node2 .
    ?node1 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?orthoProtein1 .
    ?node2 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?orthoProtein2 .
    ?orthoProtein1 lscr:xrefUniprot ?mouseProtein .
    ?orthoProtein2 lscr:xrefUniprot ?humanProtein .
    # inTaxon mouse
    ?orthoProtein1 orth:organism/<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162> taxon:10090 . 
  }
}

# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX oma: <http://omabrowser.org/ontology/oma.owl#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?humanEnzyme ?humanEnzymeName ?mouseHomolog ?mouseHomologName
WHERE {
  # UniProt: Find human enzymes
  ?humanEnzyme up:organism taxon:9606 ;
               up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction .
  OPTIONAL { ?humanEnzyme up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?humanEnzymeName . }

  # Rhea: Find reactions involving sterols (CHEBI:15889)
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
    ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
    ?chebi (rdfs:subClassOf)+ CHEBI:15889 .
  }

  # OMABrowser: Find mouse homologs of these human enzymes
  SERVICE <https://omabrowser.org/sparql> {
    # Link the human UniProt enzyme to its OMA protein entry
    ?omaProteinHuman oma:hasUniProtXref ?humanEnzyme . # ?humanEnzyme is the join variable from UniProt
    
    # Find the OMA group this human protein belongs to
    ?omaProteinHuman oma:memberOf ?omaGroup .
    
    # Find other proteins in the same OMA group
    ?omaProteinMouse oma:memberOf ?omaGroup .
    
    # Filter for mouse proteins (taxon:10090)
    ?omaProteinMouse oma:hasTaxon taxon:10090 .
    
    # Get the UniProt xref for the mouse homolog
    ?omaProteinMouse oma:hasUniProtXref ?mouseHomolog . # This is the UniProt ID of the mouse homolog
  }

  # UniProt: Get the name of the mouse homolog (from the primary endpoint)
  OPTIONAL { ?mouseHomolog up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?mouseHomologName . }
}

SELECT ?citation ?patentURI ?epoPatent ?publicationNumber ?grantDate

  ?citation a up:Patent_Citation .
  ?citation skos:exactMatch ?patentURI .

  FILTER(CONTAINS(STR(?patentURI), 'EP'))
  
  # Extract the publication number from the UniProt patent URI
  # Example: http://purl.uniprot.org/patent/EP1234567 -> EP1234567
  BIND(SUBSTR(STR(?patentURI), 35) AS ?publicationNumber)

  # Federated service call to EPO endpoint
  SERVICE <https://data.epo.org/linked-data/query> {
    # Find patents in EPO by their publication number
    ?epoPatent patent:publicationNumber ?publicationNumber .
    
    # Get the grant date for the EPO patent
    ?epoPatent patent:grantDate ?grantDate .
    
    # Filter for patents whose grant date is more than twenty years in the past
    # This means the year of the grant date must be less than (current year - 20)
    FILTER (YEAR(?grantDate) < (YEAR(NOW()) - 20))
  }
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve parent reactions (and their catalyzing enzymes) for a metabolite that is not directly involved in a reaction (ex: CHEBI:83137).
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh:<http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX ec:<http://purl.uniprot.org/enzyme/>
PREFIX up:<http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon:<http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX keywords:<http://purl.uniprot.org/keywords/>

SELECT
  ?chebi
  ?ecNumber
  (count(?protein) as ?proteinCount)
  ?reaction
  ?equation
WHERE {
  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:status rh:Approved .
  ?reaction rh:equation ?equation .
  ?reaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
  ?reaction rh:side ?reactionSide .
  ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
  CHEBI:83137 rdfs:subClassOf+ ?chebi.

  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
  ?protein a up:Protein .
  ?protein up:reviewed true .
    {?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:domain/up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:component/up:enzyme ?ecNumber} .
  }
} 
GROUP BY ?chebi ?ecNumber ?reaction ?equation
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX ec: <http://purl.uniprot.org/enzyme/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?parentReaction ?parentEquation ?ecNumber ?protein
WHERE {
  # Define the target metabolite that is not directly involved
  BIND (CHEBI:83137 AS ?targetChebi)

  # Find a compound (?involvedCompound) that is directly involved in a reaction
  # and has ?targetChebi as a reactive part or underlying component.
  # This addresses the "metabolite that is not directly involved" condition.
  ?involvedCompound (rh:reactivePart/rh:chebi | rh:underlyingChebi/rh:chebi) ?targetChebi .

  # Find a child reaction (?childReaction) where ?involvedCompound is a participant.
  ?childReaction rh:side ?reactionSide .
  ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?involvedCompound .

  # Ensure the child reaction is an approved Rhea reaction.
  ?childReaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?childReaction rh:status rh:Approved .

  # Find the parent reaction (?parentReaction) of the child reaction.
  ?childReaction rdfs:subClassOf ?parentReaction .
  ?parentReaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?parentReaction rh:status rh:Approved .
  ?parentReaction rh:equation ?parentEquation . # Retrieve the equation for the parent reaction

  # Get the EC number (?ecNumber) associated with the parent reaction.
  ?parentReaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .

  # Federate with UniProt to find proteins (enzymes) associated with the EC number.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?protein a up:Protein .
    ?protein up:reviewed true .
    # UniProt provides EC numbers through different properties, so a UNION is used.
    { ?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber . }
    UNION
    { ?protein up:domain/up:enzyme ?ecNumber . }
    UNION
    { ?protein up:component/up:enzyme ?ecNumber . }
  }
}

natural_language_question: Use IDSM Sachem to find ChEBIs with a a Cholestane skeleton (in SMILES). Then match returned ChEBIs to Rhea undirected reactions.
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX sachem: <http://bioinfo.mnis.ru/sachem/0.1/>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>

SELECT DISTINCT ?chebi ?reaction ?reactionEquation
WHERE {
  # Step 1: Use IDSM Sachem to find ChEBIs that have a Cholestane skeleton.
  # The SMILES for Cholestane (CHEBI:35516) is used for substructure search.
  SERVICE <https://idsm.elixir-czech.cz/sparql> {
    ?chebi sachem:substructureSearch "CC(C)CCCC(C)C1CCC2C3CCC4CC(C)CCC4(C)C3CCC12" .
    # It is assumed that ?chebi directly represents the ChEBI URI (e.g., http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_XXXXX)
    # as returned by IDSM Sachem for compounds matching the substructure.
  }

  # Step 2: Match the found ChEBIs to Rhea undirected reactions.
  # "Undirected reactions" in Rhea are represented by rh:BidirectionalReaction.
  ?reaction rdf:type rh:BidirectionalReaction .

  # Find compounds participating in these reactions.
  ?reaction rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?rheaCompound .

  # Link the Rhea compound to its ChEBI identifier.
  # The property path handles different ways ChEBI is linked in Rhea.
  ?rheaCompound (rh:chebi|rh:reactivePart/rh:chebi|rh:underlyingChebi/rh:chebi) ?chebi .

  # Retrieve the reaction equation for context.
  ?reaction rh:equation ?reactionEquation .
}
